HEADWORD: Snifting
<hw>Snift"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from
<er>Snift</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Snifting valve</b></col>, <cd>a small valve opening into
the atmosphere from the cylinder or condenser of a steam engine, to
allow the escape of air when the piston makes a stroke; -- so called
from the noise made by its action.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snig</ent>⟦br⟧
